      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> <strong>strips </strong>with 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Cook for 10-12 min or until golden and softened – this is your <strong>caramelised onion & pepper</strong></p>",
